      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 365: The congestion callback fires on every RTCP check while loss remains above 3%, with no hysteresis or state transition. Although video has a cooldown, every coupled video stream still receives repeated reduction requests and audio will keep logging/signaling indefinitely under sustained loss. Gate this on crossing the threshold or add an audio-side cooldown/recovery state so video is not repeatedly forced downward for the same congestion episode.",
      "revId": "b987996ce5fc6b996f0242528afcdba9cda8bcce",
