      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 635: The simulator integration is only exposed through `SocketPair::setNetworkSimulator()`, but this patch never wires `NetworkSimRegistry` to any created `SocketPair`. As a result, the README usage with `NetworkSimRegistry::getOrCreate(callId, \"audio\")` has no effect on actual RTP traffic. Either remove the registry/documentation from this change or attach the matching simulator when RTP sessions/socket pairs are configured, e.g. by looking up the call id and media type and calling `socketPair_-\u003esetNetworkSimulator(sim)`.",
