      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 807: `onAudioCongestion()` computes the new bitrate from `videoBitrateCurrent`, but if the encoder has not yet reported the previous reduction, repeated callbacks after the cooldown can recompute from a stale higher bitrate and fail to make further progress. Track the last audio-QoS target or update the local bitrate state before calling `setNewBitrate()` so consecutive congestion periods continue reducing predictably.",
      "revId": "b987996ce5fc6b996f0242528afcdba9cda8bcce",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
